org.knime.core.data

Class DataTableDomainCreator

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.knime.core.data.DataTableDomainCreator

  • public class DataTableDomainCreator
extends Object
    Create or recreate domain of a data table. The original spec has to be given in the constructor. The possible values and minimum and maximum values are subsequently updated by calling updateDomain(DataRow) or updateDomain(DataTable, ExecutionMonitor, int). Finally the resulting spec including updated domains is created by calling createSpec().
    Since:
    2.10
    Author:
    Heiko Hofer

    • Constructor Detail

      • DataTableDomainCreator

        public DataTableDomainCreator(DataTableSpec inputSpec,
                              DomainCreatorColumnSelection domainValuesColumnSelection,
                              DomainCreatorColumnSelection domainMinMaxColumnSelection)
        A new instance that recreates the domain of certains columns. Which columns are processed and if the domains should be initialized with the domain from the incoming table can be controlled by the two DomainCreatorColumnSelection arguments.
        Parameters:
        inputSpec - the spec of the input/original table
        domainValuesColumnSelection - defines columns to recreate or drop domain values
        domainMinMaxColumnSelection - defines columns to recreate or drop min, max values of the domain

      • DataTableDomainCreator

        public DataTableDomainCreator(DataTableSpec inputSpec,
                              boolean initDomain)
        A new instance that recreates the domain of all columns. Domain values are recreated for all NominalValue columns whereas min/max values are recreated for all BoundedValue columns.
        Parameters:
        inputSpec - the spec of the input/original table
        initDomain - true if the domain values should be initialized with the values from the input spec, false if the domain should be initially empty

        Set the maximum number of possible values in the domain of a nominal value columns.
        Parameters:
        maxValues - the maximal number of values, must be >= 0

      • createSpec

        public DataTableSpec createSpec()
        Creates an updated version of the input spec. The domains of all configured columns are set according to the data that has been processed by updateDomain(DataRow) or updateDomain(DataTable, ExecutionMonitor, int) so far. You may call this method multiple times even while you are still presenting more data.
        Returns:
        an updated table spec

      • updateDomain

        public void updateDomain(DataRow row)
        Updates the domain values with a single row. Note that the row structure must match the table spec that has been provided to the constructor.
        Parameters:
        row - a data row
